  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Berea-Hillbrow Home of Hope is a home caring for and educating 76 trafficked, sexually exploited and orphaned children. Beyond providing stability to these very vulnerable girls, this project is about giving back choice, dignity and the chance at a very different kind of future than the path they set out on. The home currently provides for 5 girls in daycare, 16 in primary school, 37 in high school (6 of them seniors), 8 university students and 10 peer educators, girls waiting for study funding.</narrative>
  </description>
